 for bestpractices and # Error Handling & Validation

## Overview
Implement a centralized, user-friendly error handling and validation system across the Archject platform. This includes client-side and server-side validation with graceful recovery UX, a global error handling mechanism on the backend (structured error responses and Sentry integration), robust retry/idempotency patterns for long-running operations, dedicated 404/500 pages, and integrated logging/reporting for observability. The feature underpins all associated pages (page_404, page_500, page_create_decision, page_exports) and supports a reliable export pipeline (PDF/CSV) with signed PDFs for legal use.

---

## Components to Build

- Centralized Error Handling System
  - Frontend: Global error boundary, toast/inline error messaging, validation helpers, failure recovery UI, retry controls
  - Backend: Middleware for structured error shapes, error codes, and correlation IDs; Sentry integration hooks
- Validation Framework
  - Client-side validation rules with live feedback; server-side fallback validation
  - Reusable validators for forms (Decision creation, Exports, Reminders, Attachments)
- Retry & Idempotency Layer
  - Mechanisms for long-running operations (e.g., export generation, decision package assembly) with exponential backoff, JIT retries, and idempotent endpoints
- 404 / 500 Pages
  - Fully styled, branded error pages with actionable guidance and navigation
- Create Decision Page
  - Multi-step flow (modal or page): template vs. custom, add options, attach images/drawings, designate client recipients, and configure reminder schedule
  - Real-time validation, progress tracking, autosave, and failure recovery
- Exports & Decision Logs
  - Generate downloadable packs: PDF/CSV Decision Logs, export history, and signed PDFs
  - Export pipeline with status polling, integrity checks, and error reporting
- Logging & Observability
  - Sentry integration for frontend and backend; structured error payloads; correlation IDs across requests
- Security & Compliance
  - Secure error disclosure (never reveal sensitive server details to users); authenticated/authorized access for exports; audit trails

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend

- Global Error Handling
  - Implement an ErrorBoundary component to catch uncaught runtime errors
  - Centralized error store (Redux/Context) with current error, status, and retry option
