## User Experience Flow

1) User navigates to Create Decision page
   - Chooses between a template or a custom decision
   - Validation runs for required fields (title, template selection, at least one option)

2) User adds decision options
   - Add, reorder, and modify options; validations for option names, descriptions, and visuals

3) User attaches images/drawings
   - Drag-and-drop or file picker; previews; constrained formats/sizes; upload progress shown

4) User configures recipients and reminders
   - Select client recipients; set reminder schedule with time zone awareness
   - Validation ensures valid dates and non-conflicting reminders

5) User reviews and saves draft
   - Auto-save local draft; network occurrence triggers remote save; errors surface non-destructively

6) User submits decision
   - Server validates, creates decision, and triggers notification workflow
   - On server error, UI shows friendly error with retry

7) User accesses Exports & Decision Logs
   - Configure export (PDF/CSV), select fields, and initiate export
   - Export status appears; upon completion, download signed PDF if enabled
   - If export fails, show error with retry and support guidance

8) Error scenarios
   - Network outage: inline error with retry, auto-resume when online
   - Server error: 500 page or in-context error toast with retry
   - Not found: 404 page with navigational guidance

