## Technical Specifications

- Data Models: 
  - Decision: { id, projectId, title, templateId, options: [{id, name, description, imageUrl, order}], attachments: [{id, url, type, size}], recipients: [{userId, role, status}], reminders: [{id, date, time, cadence}], status, createdAt, updatedAt, signedPdfUrl }
  - Option: { id, name, description, imageUrl, order }
  - Attachment: { id, url, type, size, uploadedAt }
  - Recipient: { userId, email, role, status }
  - Reminder: { id, date, time, cadence, timezone, sent }
  - ExportLog: { id, type, status, createdAt, completedAt, fileUrl, correlationId }
  - ErrorLog (internal): { id, message, code, correlationId, stack }

- API Endpoints:
  - POST /api/decisions (idempotent with Idempotency-Key header)
  - GET /api/decisions/{id}
  - PUT /api/decisions/{id}
  - POST /api/decisions/{id}/attachments
  - POST /api/exports/decision-logs
  - GET /api/exports/{exportId}
  - GET /api/pages/health
  - Middleware: error-handler, validation, authentication, authorization

- Security
  - OAuth2/JWT-based authentication
  - Role-based access: viewer, editor, admin; client recipients have limited view/edit rights
  - CSRF protection for state-changing requests
  - Secrets management and least-privilege for export signing service

- Validation
  - Client-side: required fields, max lengths, file type/size restrictions, date-time formats, time zones
  - Server-side: same rules, return field-level errors: { field, message, code }

- Logging & Observability
  - Sentry integration for frontend and backend
  - Structured logs with correlationId for cross-service tracing
  - Centralized error analytics with dashboards

